<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-16705] camel-spring-boot - Changing LoggingLevel for Camel Log at runtime</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-16705</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The default LogLevel is INFO. When i want to change this by spring boot actuator (JMX) to ERROR or WARN it works, but when i want to change it to DEBUG or TRACE it don&apos;t.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If I set the LogLevel at the beginning to TRACE, I can change it down to any other Level manually.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So decreasing works, but increasing the LogLevel dont.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It only applied to logging in Camel Routes. It works great on any other Logging.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In Version 3.6.0 and below it worked. All versions after that don&apos;t work anymore.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is also descibed here&#160;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/66357203/changing-camel-log-level-at-runtime-using-spring-boot-actuator|Stackoverflow&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
